Q: Angular/material ui - programatically select mat-selection-list A: <p>A bit late to the party, but this is an update for ng v18 users.</p>
<p>I actually didn't use the Selected prop on the option as making a two way binding was easier.</p>
<pre><code>&lt;mat-selection-list [multiple]=&quot;false&quot; [(ngModel)]=&quot;selectedItem&quot;                         (selectionChange)=&quot;selectionChanged($event)&quot; &gt;

     @for (addr of addresses; track addr.id) {
      &lt;mat-list-option [value]=&quot;addr&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;{{addr.addressLine1}}, {addr.locality}}&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/mat-list-option&gt;
     }
 &lt;/mat-selection-list&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>in your component define your array to iterate over</p>
<pre><code>addresses: IAddress[]
</code></pre>
<p>Mine's an object buts yours could be a primitive string[] or whatever.</p>
<p>Also define a prop for the selected option.</p>
<pre><code>selectedItem: IAddress[] = [];
</code></pre>
<p>in your constructor set the item of choice to be the default at startup.</p>
<pre><code>this.selectedItem = this.addresses.filter(x =&gt; x.addressDefault);   
</code></pre>
<p>I have a default for this array in the object itself, but you get the idea.</p>
<p>That show the list and sets a default. You could mod for multiples</p>
<p>To capture selection changes I use this method</p>
<pre><code>  selectionChanged(evt: MatSelectionListChange): void {
    this.card.selectedAddress = evt.options[0].value;   
  }
</code></pre>
<p>The prop &quot;selectedItem&quot; always has your current selections</p>
<p>If you need to dynamically add to the selection</p>
<pre><code>this.addresses = [...this.addresses, newAddress ];
this.selectedItem = [newAddress]; 
</code></pre>
<p>Add the new object to the data array and overwrite the selectedItem value.</p>
<p>Hope it helps.</p>
